records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tyler John McDonald in court with attorney Craig Michael Kuhary.  Jayne Dewire appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to count 1. Count 2 is dismissed outright. Count 3 and 4 are dismissed and read-in. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The defendant was sentenced to the following:

HUBER:  50 days, w/Standard Release Conditions. Defendant to report to Huber facility by 6:00 p.m. on  02/19/2016.

FINE: $1192.00 (to be paid at the rate of  $75.00 month commencing 04/01/2016 or serve 29 days jail, consecutive, as penalty for non payment of fine);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00, to be paid at $75.00 month consecutive to payment of fine or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of surcharge.

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to City of Waukesha Police Department or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of fee.
 
D/L REVOCATION: 14  months;

IGNITION INTERLOCK: 14 months;
 
Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH.
